<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,645,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,645,670]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This is a species of habitus and general body structures as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kormilev &amp; Froeschner" authorityYear="1987" box="[1002,1141,645,669]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Bergrothista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1141,645,669]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Bergrothista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, they lack the characteristic stridulatory structure of the latter in both sexes, for which a new genus is erected. The presence of a distinct metathoracic scent gland canal indicates that also this genus should be placed in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oshanin" authorityYear="1908" box="[1303,1420,717,741]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mezirinae">Mezirinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,645,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authority="Heiss, 2010" authorityName="Heiss" authorityYear="2010" box="[201,393,753,777]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Parabergrothista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[201,393,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Parabergrothista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[403,483,753,777]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[403,483,753,777]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles also 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoberlandt" authorityYear="1957" box="[669,778,753,777]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Jarmilaia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[669,778,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Jarmilaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance and shares the lack of stridulatory structure but is distinguished by much shorter antennae particularly segment I, by the dark coloured legs and antennae and by the thin collar.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[201,980,861,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,645,885]" box="[201,980,861,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,335,861,885]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
